---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import site from "../data/site.json";
---

<Layout>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pt-20 pb-16">
    <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium tracking-wide text-text-muted uppercase">
      {site.university}
    </p>
    <h1 class="mb-6 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
      {site.name}
    </h1>
    <p class="mb-10 max-w-xl text-lg text-text-muted">
      {site.tagline}
    </p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <a
        href="/join"
        class="inline-block rounded-md bg-text px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-cream no-underline transition-opacity hover:opacity-80"
      >
        Join the Program
      </a>
      <a
        href="/about"
        class="inline-block rounded-md border border-divider px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-text no-underline transition-colors hover:bg-cream-dark"
      >
        Learn More
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="mx-auto max-w-3xl border-divider" />

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <h2 class="mb-6 text-xl font-semibold">How It Works</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6 text-text-muted">
      <p>
        MLRP pairs undergraduates with graduate and postdoctoral researchers to read
        and discuss approximately eight machine learning-related research papers over
        the course of a quarter.
      </p>
      <p>
        Research papers are selected collaboratively by mentors and mentees. Pairs
        meet weekly at a flexible, mutually agreed-upon time throughout the quarter.
      </p>
      <p>
        At the end of the quarter, undergraduates give a short presentation on one or
        more of their favorite papers.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="mx-auto max-w-3xl border-divider" />

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16">
    <p class="italic text-text-muted">
      The program is designed to be a low-stress environment to build connections
      within the machine learning community at UW.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
